GitHub CLI (gh) - Most Likely

If you are pushing your dotfiles to GitHub, this is the modern, official way to do it. When you run its setup command, it generates a one-time code and opens your browser for you to log in.

    To install it on CachyOS/Arch:
    Bash

    sudo pacman -S github-cli

    To trigger the browser login:
    Bash

    gh auth login

    (Choose "GitHub.com" -> "HTTPS" -> "Login with a web browser")

Once you do this, Git will automatically use this authentication every time you type git push.
